WEBVTT

00:00.953 --> 00:02.349
Previously on The Resident...

00:02.359 --> 00:05.195
Dr. Benedict. My man and mentor.

00:05.206 --> 00:07.898
You led me to believe
my arrogance killed my patient.

00:07.908 --> 00:10.734
When in fact it was
a company that owns you.

00:10.744 --> 00:13.204
BELL: Every three minutes,
the QuoVadis device

00:13.214 --> 00:15.159
stopped Henry Barnett's heart.

00:15.170 --> 00:18.108
I've halted the use of all
QuoVadis devices at Chastain.

00:18.118 --> 00:21.312
QuoVadis is willing to cover Henry's
medical bills for his whole life.

00:21.322 --> 00:24.148
If you go public with a
grievance, this deal goes away.

00:24.158 --> 00:27.971
QuoVadis is engaged
in wide-ranging fraud.

00:27.982 --> 00:30.013
Our contract is now null and void.

00:30.024 --> 00:31.934
Dr. Benedict, please tell us
whatever you know.

00:31.945 --> 00:34.258
I want to talk to AJ.
He deserves the truth.

00:34.268 --> 00:35.759
GORDON: What did you tell them?

00:35.769 --> 00:37.181
I didn't tell them anything.

00:37.192 --> 00:40.063
Gordon, do you know
how I made my fortune?

00:40.074 --> 00:42.766
By taking over companies
on the verge of collapse.

00:42.776 --> 00:44.176
We should talk.

00:45.246 --> 00:47.905
(LINE RINGING)

00:47.915 --> 00:49.959
BENEDICT (ON RECORDING):
Hi, this is Dr. Benedict.

00:49.970 --> 00:52.243
I'm not in. Leave me a message
after the beep.

00:52.253 --> 00:54.345
- (BEEPS)
- Abe, it's AJ.

00:54.355 --> 00:56.146
I've been calling you all morning, man.

00:56.156 --> 00:58.349
I'm outside your house right now.

00:58.359 --> 01:01.093
I see your car in the driveway.

01:03.130 --> 01:05.022
I'm worried about you.

01:05.032 --> 01:06.965
(DOORBELL RINGS)

01:08.000 --> 01:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:22.716 --> 01:24.075
Abe?

01:25.386 --> 01:27.819
Mrs. Benedict?

01:29.723 --> 01:31.356
It's AJ.

01:36.697 --> 01:38.567
Anybody home?

01:40.034 --> 01:42.034
(CLOCK TICKING)

02:05.025 --> 02:07.025
♪ ♪

02:18.272 --> 02:20.272
No, Abe. Abe.

02:33.586 --> 02:36.012
(LINE RINGING)

02:36.023 --> 02:38.916
Fulton County 911. What is the
address of the emergency?

02:38.926 --> 02:41.012
278 Barksdale Drive.

02:41.023 --> 02:44.355
Gunshot wound. Adult male.
Thready pulse,

02:44.365 --> 02:46.357
shallow breathing.
I need an ambulance now!

02:46.367 --> 02:48.367
♪ ♪

02:55.308 --> 02:57.800
- Synced and corrected by Shazi89 -
- www.addic7ed.com -

02:57.811 --> 02:59.937
(SIREN WAILS)

02:59.947 --> 03:01.472
Male, 65.

03:01.482 --> 03:04.608
GSW, upper chest.
Severe respiratory distress.

03:04.618 --> 03:06.710
Tachy to 150.

03:06.720 --> 03:07.878
BP, 70/palp.

03:07.888 --> 03:09.146
Okay. Two units O neg.

03:09.156 --> 03:10.956
Activate massive transfusion protocol.

03:13.060 --> 03:15.285
Wait, oh, my God, is that...

03:15.295 --> 03:18.255
Yup, Dr. Abe Benedict. I found
him like this in his home.

03:18.265 --> 03:19.990
One, two, three, lift.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.759
Exit wound?

03:21.769 --> 03:24.094
- I didn't see any.
- IRVING: Let's get the portable X-ray.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.572
DEVON: No breath sounds on the left.

03:25.583 --> 03:28.322
He needs a chest tube. 32 French, to me.

03:29.109 --> 03:32.269
Chest tube kit.
And Dr. Hawkins is paged.

03:32.279 --> 03:36.615
Going in at the midaxillary line.

03:41.422 --> 03:44.589
- IRVING: Oh!
- (GRUNTING)

03:47.127 --> 03:49.787
GSW?

03:49.797 --> 03:51.422
Self-inflicted?

03:51.432 --> 03:54.124
It's hard to believe,
but it looks that way.

03:54.134 --> 03:56.794
Image is up.

03:56.804 --> 03:58.574
CONRAD: Bullet is embedded
in his abdomen.

03:58.585 --> 04:01.632
- Must have ricocheted off his ribs.
- Could've hit any number of organs.

04:01.642 --> 04:05.201
Hundley, call CT.
He needs a scan before surgery.

04:05.212 --> 04:06.644
I'll meet you up there.

04:08.882 --> 04:11.508
- Dr. Austin.
- Yeah.

04:11.518 --> 04:13.944
Listen, when you saw him,

04:13.954 --> 04:18.148
did he say anything
about QuoVadis and Gordon Page?

04:18.158 --> 04:20.559
No, he was unconscious the whole time.

04:31.572 --> 04:34.398
I am curious what

04:34.408 --> 04:36.400
the chairman of the board
of the hospital

04:36.410 --> 04:39.403
that just stabbed QuoVadis
in the back wants with me.

04:39.413 --> 04:43.240
You just lost an enormous
military contract.

04:43.250 --> 04:45.242
It's a devastating blow.

04:45.252 --> 04:47.711
We'll recover.

04:47.721 --> 04:50.247
Our devices are still
in many other hospitals.

04:50.257 --> 04:54.718
The VNS implanted at Chastain
was a horrifying failure.

04:54.728 --> 04:56.487
That's not in the public record.

04:56.497 --> 04:59.189
- The boy's mother signed an NDA.
- That certainly helps,

04:59.199 --> 05:00.924
for now.

05:00.934 --> 05:03.861
One more time. Why are you here?

05:03.871 --> 05:05.596
I'm a businessman.

05:05.606 --> 05:09.233
The medical device industry
is an unregulated gold mine.

05:09.243 --> 05:11.235
You can do almost anything.

05:11.245 --> 05:13.937
I smell an opportunity.

05:13.947 --> 05:16.206
Your company is damaged.

05:16.216 --> 05:17.708
I can help fix that.

05:17.718 --> 05:19.423
Oh, that's generous,

05:20.386 --> 05:23.476
but I've already fielded offers
from three new investors.

05:23.487 --> 05:26.488
Two, and only one of those is viable.

05:28.059 --> 05:30.659
But that investor is extremely viable.

05:31.782 --> 05:34.709
And I prefer to work
with people I can trust.

05:34.954 --> 05:38.188
Shortsighted, if not foolish.

05:47.701 --> 05:49.667
For all your outstanding shares.

05:50.484 --> 05:53.577
But I need to know

05:53.587 --> 05:55.711
where the bodies are buried.

05:55.722 --> 05:57.480
If we're going to rise together,

05:57.491 --> 05:59.883
I need to know everything.

05:59.893 --> 06:01.593
No surprises.

06:06.934 --> 06:08.333
Mm.

06:17.778 --> 06:20.005
I think you know the way out.

06:26.232 --> 06:27.652
Thank you.

06:34.161 --> 06:36.161
- (CELL PHONE BEEPS)
- (LINE RINGING)

06:38.265 --> 06:39.957
CONRAD (ON PHONE): Hello?

06:39.967 --> 06:42.025
I tried. It didn't work.

06:42.035 --> 06:43.861
Gordon Page saw right through me.

06:43.871 --> 06:46.363
He told me nothing
I didn't already know.

06:46.373 --> 06:49.466
That is not good, Dad.

06:49.476 --> 06:52.202
We have a situation here, too.

06:52.212 --> 06:55.873
Abe Benedict just came into our ER.

06:55.883 --> 06:57.374
He tried to kill himself.

06:58.481 --> 06:59.943
Do we know why?

06:59.953 --> 07:01.945
No. And he may never wake up.

07:02.763 --> 07:05.382
In which case we'll never find out
what he knows about QuoVadis.

07:05.392 --> 07:07.718
Well, I did find out Page has

07:07.728 --> 07:09.519
another investor looking to make a deal.

07:09.529 --> 07:10.988
He gets that money,

07:10.998 --> 07:13.357
QuoVadis will be back
in business in no time.

07:14.390 --> 07:16.226
We need to stop that.

07:16.236 --> 07:17.961
Do you know who the investor is?

07:17.971 --> 07:21.198
I have a pretty good idea.

07:22.458 --> 07:24.167
You need to meet with him

07:24.177 --> 07:26.904
and you need to scare him off.

07:26.914 --> 07:30.040
- I can try.
- Good.

07:30.050 --> 07:33.343
And I'll do everything I can
to keep Abe Benedict alive.

07:34.286 --> 07:36.520
Good luck, Conrad.

07:43.230 --> 07:46.323
Studying for this final
is making my brain hurt.

07:46.333 --> 07:48.492
Well, humor heals all.

07:48.502 --> 07:51.261
What do engineers use for birth control?

07:51.271 --> 07:54.031
Um, their personalities.

07:54.041 --> 07:56.233
- (BOTH LAUGH)
- (SNORTS)

07:56.243 --> 07:57.701
(COUGHING)

07:57.711 --> 07:59.714
- Pretty funny, you guys.
- SYDNEY: Oh, Nurse Nevin,

07:59.725 --> 08:01.672
- you're back.
- Did our test results come in?

08:01.682 --> 08:04.007
They did. Uh, why don't
you guys follow me.

08:05.622 --> 08:08.607
The good news is you can
both ask for an extension

08:08.618 --> 08:10.975
on your engineering final.

08:10.986 --> 08:14.417
The bad news is... you both have mono.

08:14.428 --> 08:15.619
Mono?

08:15.629 --> 08:17.587
Wait, how'd we both get mono?

08:17.597 --> 08:20.457
Well, they don't call it "the
kissing disease" for nothing.

08:20.468 --> 08:23.191
Oh. (CHUCKLES) No, uh,

08:23.202 --> 08:26.206
- we're just friends.
- Best friends. Together since...

08:26.217 --> 08:29.433
Since she blocked off the seesaw
to explain the relationship

08:29.443 --> 08:31.735
between distance and mass
to our kindergarten class.

08:31.745 --> 08:35.105
But not together-together,
you know, it's-it's more like...

08:35.115 --> 08:36.606
Like study buddies, but definitely...

08:36.616 --> 08:38.542
- Not a couple. No.
- No.

08:38.552 --> 08:40.977
Uh, okay. Well, my mistake.

08:40.988 --> 08:43.046
Um, but there are other ways
you can contract mono.

08:43.056 --> 08:44.715
I mean, if you use the same toothbrush,

08:44.725 --> 08:47.384
- sharing food...
- We've done that a lot lately.

08:47.394 --> 08:50.510
Cramming for finals.
All pizza, all the time.

08:50.521 --> 08:52.222
- (CHUCKLES)
- Okay. Well, you can both

08:52.232 --> 08:53.490
go back to your dorms.

08:53.500 --> 08:56.059
Uh, you'll want plenty of sleep, fluids.

08:56.069 --> 08:58.562
Mono's not usually a big deal, but, uh,

08:58.572 --> 09:00.397
you'll definitely want a ton of rest.

09:00.407 --> 09:02.440
- Thank you. That's a relief.
- (COUGHING)

09:04.832 --> 09:07.804
Um, Evan, just... humor me.

09:07.814 --> 09:10.228
I-I want to check something quickly.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.328
Your finger?

09:13.453 --> 09:14.853
(MONITOR BEEPING)

09:16.423 --> 09:19.583
Hm. O2 sat is 88%.

09:19.593 --> 09:22.285
That's, um, significantly lower
than when you came in.

09:22.295 --> 09:24.254
- And what does that mean?
- Uh, it means

09:24.264 --> 09:27.624
that I actually can't
send you home just yet.

09:27.634 --> 09:29.666
Um, Sydney, you're welcome to go,

09:29.677 --> 09:32.010
unless you want to stay.

09:34.256 --> 09:35.847
I'll stick around.

09:35.858 --> 09:38.504
Can't catch something
I already have, right?

09:38.515 --> 09:40.378
I'll be right back.

09:42.130 --> 09:44.893
We need to admit Evan Weston
to Chastain immediately.

09:45.952 --> 09:47.944
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

09:47.954 --> 09:50.188
SYDNEY: You've never even
kissed a girl in your life.

10:02.903 --> 10:04.903
OR One is prepped and ready.

10:08.909 --> 10:10.909
I'm sorry about your friend.

10:14.047 --> 10:17.090
Abe taught me everything I know.

10:17.751 --> 10:19.350
(DOOR OPENS)

10:21.592 --> 10:24.247
When you saw him yesterday at
the conference, how did he seem?

10:24.725 --> 10:25.950
MINA: Intoxicated.

10:26.469 --> 10:27.584
Nervous.

10:27.594 --> 10:30.887
He was struggling. Whatever
he knew, whatever he did,

10:30.897 --> 10:33.023
the guilt was starting
to eat away at him.

10:33.033 --> 10:35.358
Are you thinking this wasn't
a suicide attempt?

10:35.368 --> 10:37.260
- Yeah.
- I think Gordon tried

10:37.270 --> 10:40.030
to have him silenced.

10:40.040 --> 10:42.866
You're suggesting Gordon
had Abe Benedict shot?

10:42.876 --> 10:47.340
Well, I would believe that over Abe
putting a bullet in his own chest.

10:47.351 --> 10:50.040
He was a heart surgeon. He knew
where to aim if he wanted to die.

10:50.050 --> 10:52.212
And suicide just doesn't fit
the man I know.

10:52.223 --> 10:56.143
Abe jogged every night on
two bad knees to keep healthy.

10:56.154 --> 10:57.414
The man loved life.

10:57.424 --> 10:59.382
But he also took $1
million from QuoVadis.

10:59.392 --> 11:01.384
That didn't fit the
man you knew, either.

11:01.394 --> 11:03.553
Well, doctors commit suicide.

11:03.563 --> 11:05.889
It happens. More than
we'd like to admit.

11:05.899 --> 11:07.390
DEVON: This is too coincidental.

11:07.400 --> 11:09.126
This, on top of what happened to Julian,

11:09.136 --> 11:11.928
and we still don't
even know where she is.

11:11.938 --> 11:14.397
MINA: Looks like the bullet
hit the spleen and kidney.

11:14.407 --> 11:15.699
It clipped his heart as well.

11:15.709 --> 11:17.067
.22 caliber.

11:17.077 --> 11:19.202
Sometimes a bullet has enough
power to enter the body,

11:19.212 --> 11:20.770
but not enough to go through.

11:20.780 --> 11:23.222
Yeah, I've seen a bullet enter
a lung and end up in a leg.

11:23.233 --> 11:26.243
You know, if we save his life,
we can get some answers.

11:26.253 --> 11:28.311
Let's scrub in.

11:28.875 --> 11:30.341
Keep me updated.

11:39.027 --> 11:40.860
His hand is moving.

11:42.709 --> 11:45.781
Sedation is too light. Bolus 50 of
propofol and increase the rate.

11:45.792 --> 11:48.827
Dr. Benedict? Can you hear me?

11:50.343 --> 11:52.844
Whoa, whoa.
He's trying to say something.

11:54.848 --> 11:57.115
Don't let him pull out
his tube, he could arrest.

12:01.366 --> 12:04.347
- Damn it.
- Keep the propofol at that rate.

12:04.357 --> 12:06.785
We can't force Abe to speak
or do anything else

12:06.796 --> 12:09.719
that would harm our patient. Stay
focused. We need to put saving his life

12:09.737 --> 12:12.371
above everything else.
Get him to the OR now.

12:15.565 --> 12:18.699
MINA: The bullet hit the spleen and the
left kidney. Actively hemorrhaging.

12:18.710 --> 12:21.533
- There's no time for repair.
- I'll resect the spleen.

12:21.544 --> 12:23.044
AUSTIN: Go.

12:23.913 --> 12:25.913
Will you look at that?

12:30.387 --> 12:33.054
Insidious devil.

12:35.687 --> 12:37.925
Spleen is out. Bleeding controlled.

12:39.296 --> 12:41.438
He's acidotic and coagulopathic.

12:41.449 --> 12:44.301
If you cut him any more,
he's not coming off that table.

12:44.942 --> 12:47.460
- Damage control surgery?
- Yeah.

12:47.470 --> 12:51.064
Now listen up. We wrap him,
but we do not close.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.565
Take him out and let him heal,

12:52.575 --> 12:54.242
and we bring him back when he's ready.

13:11.728 --> 13:13.687
- You couldn't close?
- No?

13:14.710 --> 13:16.867
The amount of surgery he needs
to fix everything

13:16.878 --> 13:19.959
would be too much for a body
to handle in one go.

13:19.969 --> 13:21.795
How long until you can go back in?

13:21.805 --> 13:23.863
It's a long range.

13:23.873 --> 13:25.940
Could be hours, could be days.

13:27.362 --> 13:29.662
This is not the outcome we wanted.

13:32.649 --> 13:34.474
Formula for stress?

13:34.484 --> 13:36.209
(EXHALES)

13:36.219 --> 13:39.012
Sigma equals... (EXHALES)

13:40.608 --> 13:42.182
applied force over...

13:42.192 --> 13:44.718
(EXHALES) Can't concentrate.

13:44.728 --> 13:47.781
We don't need to do this. Please.
You need to rest.

13:48.377 --> 13:51.223
Can't. Too hard to breathe. (EXHALES)

13:51.234 --> 13:54.802
If I fall asleep...
I'm afraid I won't wake up.

13:56.339 --> 13:57.964
Sydney, Evan.

13:57.974 --> 13:59.366
This is Dr. Hawkins.

13:59.376 --> 14:01.738
We're gonna take a closer look at you.

14:01.749 --> 14:04.336
- Hello.
- Double mono patients.

14:04.354 --> 14:06.469
Sydney is stable, but Evan is hypoxic.

14:06.480 --> 14:09.309
Chest X-ray was just done, and
we're waiting on the results.

14:09.319 --> 14:10.977
But I think we need to up the O2.

14:10.987 --> 14:14.536
Look, please help him.
He's getting much worse.

14:15.258 --> 14:17.525
(WHEEZING)

14:19.596 --> 14:21.654
Yeah, we should crank up the O2.

14:21.664 --> 14:24.689
And let's order a breathing treatment.

14:25.869 --> 14:27.648
I like the dedication.

14:27.975 --> 14:29.929
Still studying when you feel this lousy.

14:29.939 --> 14:31.731
Finals.

14:31.741 --> 14:33.174
Mechanical engineering.

14:34.749 --> 14:37.170
We're gonna design a... high-speed train

14:37.180 --> 14:40.036
from... Atlanta to Nashville.

14:40.047 --> 14:41.508
So he can go home on the weekends.

14:41.518 --> 14:43.676
That's where we're both from.

14:43.686 --> 14:46.220
(COUGHING)

14:48.027 --> 14:50.745
Why is Evan so much worse
when we both have mono?

14:50.756 --> 14:52.815
The truth is, it's hard to know.

14:52.826 --> 14:54.888
Each person reacts differently
to a virus.

14:54.898 --> 14:56.564
But he's gonna be okay, right?

14:56.575 --> 15:00.176
Um, just one second...

15:02.699 --> 15:05.500
(QUIETLY): His X-ray's back.
This is really bad.

15:08.778 --> 15:10.737
All right, let's get him to the ICU.

15:10.747 --> 15:12.213
Okay.

15:13.883 --> 15:15.909
Let's start him on ceftriaxone
and azithromycin.

15:15.919 --> 15:18.445
Call respiratory. Put him on
a BiPap when we get to the unit.

15:18.455 --> 15:20.580
And I need another full set
of labs with a blood gas.

15:20.590 --> 15:22.549
Yes, Doctor.

15:22.559 --> 15:25.318
ICU? That's bad, isn't it?

15:25.328 --> 15:27.587
Well, his mono's caused him
to develop pneumonia.

15:27.597 --> 15:29.589
- Pneumonia?
- Don't worry. Don't worry.

15:29.599 --> 15:31.424
Listen, let's just try to stay calm

15:31.434 --> 15:33.493
so we can be there for Evan. Okay?

15:33.503 --> 15:35.929
Okay. Calm.

15:35.939 --> 15:39.799
Not one of my best traits,
but I can do it for him.

15:39.847 --> 15:42.348
You got this. Here, come with me.

15:44.013 --> 15:46.280
MAN (OVER P.A.): Dr. Friedman,
please call Recovery.

15:48.742 --> 15:50.816
- Lactate levels?
- Coming down.

15:50.827 --> 15:53.366
- Most recent hematocrit?
- 24% stable.

15:53.377 --> 15:56.188
- But there was a lot of trauma.
- Can we take him back to surgery now?

15:56.199 --> 15:58.524
He needs time for
his hemodynamics to stabilize.

15:58.535 --> 16:00.815
MINA: His IVC is leaking. We
need to repair it quickly.

16:00.826 --> 16:03.523
- Our first pass was crude.
- We bring him back in now,

16:03.533 --> 16:05.758
- I don't think he makes it.
- We need to decide. Soon.

16:05.768 --> 16:07.702
I know, Mina.

16:10.738 --> 16:12.455
How's he doing?

16:14.939 --> 16:17.774
If we dialed back his sedatives, do
you think he'd be able to speak?

16:17.785 --> 16:19.472
That's inappropriate, Pravesh.

16:19.482 --> 16:21.251
It wouldn't hurt him.
And it might even...

16:21.262 --> 16:23.443
You are too close to this case.

16:23.453 --> 16:25.152
And you're not?

16:29.692 --> 16:32.693
Go back to the ER, Pravesh.

16:34.026 --> 16:35.725
I will keep you updated.

16:46.142 --> 16:47.200
Book an OR.

16:47.210 --> 16:49.068
We'll give him a half hour,

16:49.078 --> 16:52.013
we'll go back into surgery,
and we'll finish the job.

16:58.588 --> 17:00.580
(MONITOR BEEPING QUICKLY)

17:00.590 --> 17:02.982
Mono patient in the ICU.

17:02.992 --> 17:05.685
Nurse says he's spiraling down.

17:05.694 --> 17:07.819
- (GASPING)
- SYDNEY: Evan? Evan?!

17:07.829 --> 17:09.222
NIC: What's going on?

17:09.233 --> 17:10.676
It's like he's drowning. Help him!

17:10.688 --> 17:12.221
NIC: Get him up.

17:14.204 --> 17:15.969
He has crackles throughout his lungs.

17:15.980 --> 17:17.396
BiPap isn't enough.

17:17.406 --> 17:19.866
- He needs a vent.
- Please, what does that mean?

17:19.876 --> 17:21.781
He can't breathe on his own
anymore, so the vent

17:21.792 --> 17:24.957
- will breathe for him.
- Evan, I'm here. I won't leave you.

17:24.968 --> 17:27.707
- We need to intubate now.
- I'm already on it. I paged RT.

17:27.717 --> 17:28.841
You need to wait outside.

17:28.851 --> 17:30.076
I want to stay with him.

17:30.086 --> 17:31.578
I'll come get you when he's settled.

17:31.588 --> 17:32.703
(GASPING CONTINUES)

17:32.723 --> 17:34.452
(CRYING): Evan...

17:35.949 --> 17:37.982
Here. Pass it over.

17:47.731 --> 17:49.322
(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

17:51.397 --> 17:53.123
AUSTIN: Exposing the heart

17:53.133 --> 17:56.033
and the abdominal contents.

18:06.418 --> 18:07.700
MINA: Removing the packs.

18:07.711 --> 18:09.044
14 in total?

18:09.054 --> 18:12.756
AUSTIN: Proceeding to repair the IVC.

18:13.759 --> 18:16.252
Just keep it going.

18:16.262 --> 18:18.754
Keep it steady. Keep it.

18:18.764 --> 18:20.430
Keep it steady. Keep it going. Keep it.

18:24.570 --> 18:26.428
Take a step back.

18:26.438 --> 18:28.430
Clear your head.

18:28.440 --> 18:30.774
I have this.

18:34.813 --> 18:37.439
(AUSTIN BREATHES DEEPLY)

18:37.449 --> 18:39.449
(SINGING PROLONGED NOTE)

18:49.161 --> 18:50.586
(GRUNTS)

18:50.596 --> 18:52.121
(BEATBOXES)

18:52.131 --> 18:53.756
(SIGHS)

18:53.766 --> 18:55.190
Back in the game?

18:55.200 --> 18:57.868
Back in the game, baby. (LAUGHS)

18:58.938 --> 19:00.329
Works every time.

19:00.339 --> 19:01.764
You should try it.

19:01.774 --> 19:04.667
Oh, not in this lifetime, but thanks.

19:04.677 --> 19:07.671
You know, it's just now hitting me,

19:08.314 --> 19:11.307
despite my disappointment,

19:11.317 --> 19:13.218
how much Abe means to me.

19:13.601 --> 19:17.454
And I am gonna give him a shot
at redemption.

19:28.459 --> 19:30.426
Howard Loomis.

19:32.037 --> 19:34.257
- Do I know you?
- Marshall Winthrop.

19:34.268 --> 19:36.063
Oh, of course. We met at the, uh,

19:36.074 --> 19:38.133
Signature CEO Conference in Boca.

19:38.143 --> 19:41.436
Yes. And you run CliffCrest Management,

19:41.446 --> 19:43.405
- a hedge fund out of Miami.
- I do.

19:43.415 --> 19:45.840
I heard whispers that you made
a special trip here

19:45.850 --> 19:47.409
to see Gordon Page.

19:47.419 --> 19:48.944
I'm, uh, I'm late for another meeting.

19:48.954 --> 19:50.111
Is there a point to this?

19:50.121 --> 19:52.013
Just giving you fair warning.

19:52.023 --> 19:54.316
The bad news is not all out
on this company.

19:54.326 --> 19:56.585
A whistle-blower
was going to come forward,

19:56.595 --> 19:58.820
a prominent doctor on the inside.

19:58.830 --> 20:00.088
And?

20:00.098 --> 20:01.957
Well, this morning he showed up

20:01.967 --> 20:06.135
in the Chastain Park ER
with a bullet in his chest.

20:07.706 --> 20:09.698
What-what are you saying?

20:09.708 --> 20:13.368
Just that it may or may not
have been self-inflicted.

20:13.378 --> 20:16.471
Gordon Page is a dangerous man.

20:16.481 --> 20:19.441
Not someone
you want to do business with.

20:19.451 --> 20:23.044
I'm sorry. I'm sorry,
but when a man like you

20:23.054 --> 20:25.513
tracks down a man like me
with information like this,

20:25.523 --> 20:27.816
then I start wondering.

20:27.826 --> 20:29.351
What my angle is?

20:29.361 --> 20:32.387
To stop a monster
from destroying more lives.

20:32.397 --> 20:36.057
For men like you and me,
it's usually all about money,

20:36.067 --> 20:39.369
but with this one, it's
simply about doing what's right.

20:43.808 --> 20:45.667
(MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY)

20:45.677 --> 20:48.637
His O2 sats keep going down even
though we've gone up on the vent.

20:48.647 --> 20:51.647
All right, there's something new going
on. Pull up his most recent X-rays.

20:53.704 --> 20:55.644
God. He has new bilateral infiltrates.

20:55.654 --> 20:57.486
His lungs are inflamed.

21:00.454 --> 21:03.359
It's too much trauma from the
bullet and the surgeries.

21:05.196 --> 21:06.921
ARDS.

21:06.931 --> 21:09.198
What do we do now?

21:10.235 --> 21:13.367
(MONITOR BEEPING QUICKLY)

21:13.378 --> 21:15.497
He's maxed out on his vent setting.
What now?

21:15.507 --> 21:17.999
Nic, if his lungs are failing,
he won't live long.

21:18.009 --> 21:21.077
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

21:21.088 --> 21:22.537
He needs ECMO.

21:22.547 --> 21:24.247
Yep.

21:25.283 --> 21:27.083
I'm on it.

21:28.119 --> 21:29.844
Is he dying?

21:29.987 --> 21:32.254
(EXHALES)

21:34.981 --> 21:37.185
The virus is making his lungs very sick.

21:37.195 --> 21:39.854
Even the vent isn't getting him
the oxygen that he needs.

21:39.864 --> 21:41.923
You have to save him. Please.

21:41.933 --> 21:43.591
We have a plan.

21:43.601 --> 21:45.593
And I promise we're not gonna give up.

21:45.603 --> 21:47.395
I screwed up.

21:47.405 --> 21:49.764
I was too afraid
to tell him how I really feel,

21:49.774 --> 21:51.507
and now I might not get the chance.

21:53.468 --> 21:55.468
You're in love with him.

21:55.747 --> 21:57.806
(SIGHS)

21:57.816 --> 22:02.210
Last summer, I went to this
engineering intensive at Duke.

22:02.220 --> 22:06.081
Thought I would set up my future
and make friends.

22:06.900 --> 22:09.551
Then I got there, and I... didn't.

22:09.561 --> 22:11.653
I didn't even try.

22:11.663 --> 22:14.622
I spent all day wishing

22:14.632 --> 22:16.632
I could see Evan.

22:18.069 --> 22:20.795
I quit after two weeks.

22:20.805 --> 22:24.232
Told my family I was just homesick.

22:24.242 --> 22:29.499
But the truth was...
I was homesick for him.

22:31.282 --> 22:33.675
I never told him how I really felt

22:33.686 --> 22:37.788
'cause I didn't want
to ruin our friendship.

22:38.957 --> 22:41.017
And now,

22:41.993 --> 22:44.064
it might be too late.

22:51.081 --> 22:53.136
We're gonna do our best.

22:54.527 --> 22:55.897
CONRAD: What's happening with Abe?

22:55.908 --> 22:57.911
Nothing good. His lungs are failing.

22:57.922 --> 23:00.780
(SIGHS) I have a patient, Evan
Weston, -who needs to go on ECMO.

23:00.791 --> 23:02.818
We're having the same
discussion about Abe.

23:02.829 --> 23:05.088
Yeah, well,
the hospital has two machines.

23:05.099 --> 23:07.275
I'll see if they're available.

23:07.285 --> 23:09.310
(STAMMERS) ECMO? What is that?

23:09.320 --> 23:12.647
BOLTON: ECMO stands for
extracorporeal membrane oxygenation.

23:12.657 --> 23:14.883
It's a machine that's used
when a patient's lungs

23:14.893 --> 23:16.484
are severely damaged, and the vent

23:16.494 --> 23:18.553
isn't providing enough oxygen for them.

23:18.563 --> 23:20.355
Is it dangerous?

23:20.365 --> 23:22.365
This move is very risky.

23:23.835 --> 23:25.393
(CONRAD EXHALES)

23:25.403 --> 23:28.137
This is a last-ditch effort.

23:30.175 --> 23:32.333
BOLTON: We'll have to get
the parents' consent.

23:32.343 --> 23:35.570
Chastain does have two machines,
but one's taken.

23:35.580 --> 23:37.338
Has been for a week.

23:37.348 --> 23:39.574
Great. So we have two patients
who need ECMO

23:39.584 --> 23:41.409
if they have any chance to live.

23:41.419 --> 23:43.342
And only one will get it.

23:44.459 --> 23:45.847
How do we choose?

23:46.683 --> 23:48.149
Can we transfer one of these patients

23:48.159 --> 23:50.552
- to a different hospital?
- They're both too sick.

23:50.562 --> 23:52.359
- They wouldn't survive transport.
- There must be

23:52.370 --> 23:53.988
a spare machine somewhere in Atlanta.

23:53.998 --> 23:55.990
I called. All of the ones
in the city are in use.

23:56.000 --> 23:57.919
The closest one is Louisville.
That's a day's drive away.

23:57.930 --> 24:00.061
- Someone has to play God.
- Abe needs the machine

24:00.071 --> 24:01.856
in the next 30 minutes.

24:01.867 --> 24:03.565
So does Evan.

24:03.575 --> 24:06.100
Abe Benedict
is a world-renowned surgeon.

24:06.110 --> 24:07.936
He's got at least 20 years to live,

24:07.946 --> 24:10.505
which means he can teach
hundreds of budding surgeons

24:10.515 --> 24:12.574
during that time.
Saving Abe will be saving

24:12.584 --> 24:14.843
- many lives.
- He's also a possible suicide.

24:14.853 --> 24:16.924
Look, I'm sorry, but are
we really gonna give this

24:16.935 --> 24:18.713
to the 60-year-old man
who might not even want to live?

24:18.723 --> 24:20.215
Abe did not attempt suicide.

24:20.225 --> 24:23.218
Evan Weston is a 22-year-old kid.

24:23.228 --> 24:25.220
- He's got his whole life...
- Look, just... look, hang on a second.

24:25.230 --> 24:27.722
Everybody in this room has
a personal stake in the outcome.

24:27.732 --> 24:29.257
It's already a major conflict.

24:29.267 --> 24:31.626
I think we should keep
emotions out of this.

24:31.636 --> 24:34.062
- So what are you proposing?
- Statistics.

24:34.072 --> 24:35.530
At this point in their lives,

24:35.540 --> 24:37.398
Evan Weston has the most years
to gain. He should get

24:37.409 --> 24:39.591
- the machine.
- Well, and there's another consideration.

24:39.602 --> 24:41.202
The patient has to survive ECMO.

24:41.212 --> 24:43.238
Evan's young, he's far stronger.

24:43.248 --> 24:48.042
Abe just had major surgery.

24:49.244 --> 24:53.313
I am sure that Evan is a great kid,
and no one wants to see him die.

24:53.324 --> 24:57.285
But Abe Benedict has damning
information about QuoVadis...

24:57.295 --> 24:59.834
and Gordon Page, the man
who may have had Julian killed.

24:59.845 --> 25:02.604
Okay, that is a speculation.
I mean, you said so yourself.

25:02.615 --> 25:05.649
(SIGHS) No one wants to take
down QuoVadis more than I do,

25:05.660 --> 25:08.627
but Mina's right.

25:09.407 --> 25:11.574
We need to keep emotions out of this.

25:14.309 --> 25:15.769
Evan Weston goes on ECMO.

25:15.780 --> 25:17.480
That's the decision.

25:31.534 --> 25:34.360
It looks like Abe Benedict
will never regain consciousness.

25:34.371 --> 25:37.097
Hmm. I'm sorry to hear that.

25:37.478 --> 25:39.837
Did you speak to Gordon's
investor like I suggested?

25:39.847 --> 25:44.283
Howard Loomis had
a crisis of conscience.

25:45.920 --> 25:47.945
Yes, he did.

25:47.955 --> 25:50.581
Gordon is scrambling,
but that means nothing

25:50.591 --> 25:54.193
unless we can use his
desperation to take him down.

25:55.262 --> 25:56.954
I'm listening.

25:56.964 --> 26:00.858
I go back in, bluff, make him believe

26:00.868 --> 26:02.760
Abe Benedict told us everything we need.

26:02.770 --> 26:04.495
No way. You're not doing that.

26:04.505 --> 26:06.297
I'll be wired this time.

26:06.307 --> 26:08.633
The FBI is close.

26:08.643 --> 26:11.602
They want him just as bad as we do.

26:11.612 --> 26:14.772
Son, this is the time.

26:14.782 --> 26:16.889
If we don't seize this opportunity,

26:16.900 --> 26:18.643
Gordon gets away with everything,

26:18.653 --> 26:21.345
- he rebuilds his empire.
- (SIGHS)

26:22.167 --> 26:25.101
Trust me,
he'll find the money somewhere.

26:29.530 --> 26:31.530
Okay.

26:38.706 --> 26:40.572
Dad.

26:42.810 --> 26:44.810
Be careful.

26:53.921 --> 26:56.347
This is a recording device,

26:56.357 --> 26:59.917
and it will get every word
spoken within a 20-foot radius.

26:59.927 --> 27:01.927
Got it.

27:04.398 --> 27:06.524
Just stick to the script.

27:06.534 --> 27:11.195
And remember, if you get
in trouble, we're listening.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.547
And we can get to you
in under five minutes.

27:41.135 --> 27:43.135
♪ ♪

28:03.318 --> 28:04.976
NIC: How you doing?

28:04.987 --> 28:07.785
It just all looks so terrifying.

28:07.795 --> 28:10.588
Is that machine really gonna
help him breathe?

28:10.598 --> 28:14.291
His lungs will barely move,
but that's because the machine

28:14.301 --> 28:16.668
is actually breathing for him.

28:17.738 --> 28:19.004
(EXHALES)

28:20.608 --> 28:23.026
Look, why don't we get you
set up in the family room?

28:23.037 --> 28:24.437
This could take a while.

28:29.016 --> 28:31.175
When he wakes up...

28:32.052 --> 28:33.685
if he wakes up...

28:35.692 --> 28:38.182
I'm gonna tell him how I feel.

28:38.192 --> 28:40.926
I think that's a good idea.

28:43.094 --> 28:45.094
Come on.

28:54.441 --> 28:56.257
Things got...

28:58.095 --> 29:00.546
complicated, lately.

29:03.951 --> 29:08.554
Never in a million years did I
think we would end up like this.

29:18.118 --> 29:20.552
I'm sorry, brother.

29:36.186 --> 29:38.151
AUSTIN: Ready to put Evan on ECMO?

29:38.170 --> 29:40.373
- We're all set.
- All right. Let's do it.

30:03.166 --> 30:05.900
♪ ♪

30:20.728 --> 30:25.087
MINA: Oxygen saturation is up.
We're at 92%.

30:25.098 --> 30:28.177
AUSTIN: Nic Nevin probably
just saved your life.

30:28.188 --> 30:30.521
Live long and prosper.

30:35.526 --> 30:37.926
We still have work to do.

30:40.376 --> 30:42.334
I've already upped his PEEP to 18.

30:42.345 --> 30:43.974
No, easy on his lungs.

30:43.984 --> 30:45.643
Push too much, they'll pop.

30:45.653 --> 30:48.287
He's still hypoxemic.

30:52.226 --> 30:54.885
He's showing signs
of multisystem organ failure.

30:55.692 --> 30:57.592
How can I help?

30:57.831 --> 30:59.831
I got nothing.

31:06.076 --> 31:08.076
Well, what if...

31:09.386 --> 31:10.618
Wait!

31:11.679 --> 31:16.340
Maybe we just need to change
his point of view on the world.

31:16.350 --> 31:18.943
Well, I'm open to suggestions.
Good ones, at least.

31:19.859 --> 31:20.978
We prone him.

31:20.988 --> 31:23.781
Turn him over,
let gravity force more oxygen

31:23.791 --> 31:25.416
into the rest of his lungs.

31:25.426 --> 31:27.251
He just had major abdominal surgery.

31:27.261 --> 31:29.520
You turn him upside down,
his incisions will tear.

31:29.530 --> 31:32.589
His insides will spill onto
the floor... literally, Pravesh.

31:32.599 --> 31:35.184
Let's make sure they don't.
We'll tighten his bandages.

31:35.195 --> 31:38.028
Come on, he's in respiratory failure.
What else do we have to lose?

31:38.038 --> 31:39.671
I say we go with Dr. Pravesh's plan.

31:43.821 --> 31:45.021
Okay.

31:45.032 --> 31:47.504
Let's call and order the rotating bed.

31:47.521 --> 31:48.721
Okay.

31:57.940 --> 31:59.740
Strap him in, wrap him up.

32:21.600 --> 32:22.787
Secured.

32:23.993 --> 32:25.057
All right.

32:25.931 --> 32:28.202
Turn him over, nice and slow.

32:31.591 --> 32:33.574
(WHIRRING)

32:52.161 --> 32:53.594
(DOOR OPENS)

32:58.768 --> 33:02.628
Loomis has decided to take
his money elsewhere.

33:02.638 --> 33:05.498
I do whatever it takes
to get what I want.

33:05.508 --> 33:08.467
Hmm. I can appreciate that.

33:08.477 --> 33:12.338
Good, because I'm still willing
to make an offer.

33:13.453 --> 33:15.241
Same number as before?

33:15.251 --> 33:17.813
No, that was when you had options.

33:17.824 --> 33:21.614
I was paying a hefty premium
then to compete.

33:21.624 --> 33:25.184
I'm offering less now,
but still a substantial sum.

33:25.194 --> 33:28.154
No. No. Why should I take that?

33:28.164 --> 33:30.464
Because you don't have a choice.

33:31.834 --> 33:34.760
Men like you and I always have choices.

33:35.548 --> 33:38.297
I can walk, fold the company,

33:38.307 --> 33:40.800
raise capital and reinvent myself.

33:40.810 --> 33:43.435
Start over somewhere else.

33:43.445 --> 33:45.771
It's my specialty.

33:45.781 --> 33:47.640
MARSHALL: Agreed.

33:47.650 --> 33:50.109
But when I bury someone,
I make sure they're firmly

33:50.119 --> 33:53.546
in the ground where nobody
can hear them scream.

33:53.556 --> 33:56.182
You didn't do that.

33:57.145 --> 34:01.519
Right now, Abe Benedict is in
a hospital room at Chastain.

34:01.530 --> 34:06.125
The air filling his lungs
is allowing his mouth to move.

34:06.135 --> 34:08.159
He's talking.

34:08.170 --> 34:11.964
Trust me, he's saying things
that leave you

34:11.974 --> 34:14.699
only one choice.

34:14.710 --> 34:16.467
I don't believe you.

34:16.478 --> 34:20.306
You don't now, but you soon will.

34:20.315 --> 34:23.542
In 15 minutes, lights will
start flashing outside.

34:23.552 --> 34:26.344
They will have a warrant
for your arrest.

34:26.355 --> 34:28.547
Take my money and disappear.

34:28.556 --> 34:31.150
I will run QuoVadis without you.

34:31.159 --> 34:32.918
Go hide out on an island somewhere

34:32.928 --> 34:35.688
without extradition laws to the U.S.

34:35.697 --> 34:37.223
Live large.

34:37.647 --> 34:39.947
That's as good as an admission of guilt.

34:40.569 --> 34:41.867
I don't care.

34:43.578 --> 34:45.706
Best and final.

34:51.936 --> 34:53.081
Call him.

34:53.984 --> 34:55.226
Who?

34:56.887 --> 34:58.569
Your son.

35:00.944 --> 35:03.782
There are some details
I'd like to know from Abe,

35:03.792 --> 35:06.426
now that he can talk.

35:09.064 --> 35:10.789
O2 sats are no better.

35:10.799 --> 35:12.892
It takes a few minutes
for gravity to do its job.

35:12.902 --> 35:15.194
Yeah, well, he doesn't have
a few minutes.

35:15.204 --> 35:18.297
- Is your dad...?
- Going to QuoVadis, yes.

35:18.307 --> 35:20.719
We're taking one last shot
at bringing down Gordon.

35:20.730 --> 35:22.786
- Have you heard from him?
- No.

35:22.797 --> 35:25.804
Guys. O2 sats are rising.

35:25.815 --> 35:27.613
88.

35:30.285 --> 35:31.405
92.

35:31.416 --> 35:33.883
It's working.

35:41.364 --> 35:44.656
I know. I know you're thinking
we should back off the sedation

35:44.667 --> 35:47.126
to see if we can get him to talk.

35:48.277 --> 35:49.895
Don't you?

35:49.905 --> 35:53.499
Abe wakes up and bucks his vent,
his O2 sats will crater.

35:53.509 --> 35:55.902
MINA: You said so yourself,

35:55.913 --> 35:59.481
Abe Benedict needs
a chance at redemption.

36:06.088 --> 36:07.988
Dial back the propofol.

36:13.362 --> 36:15.362
(BEEPING)

36:26.623 --> 36:28.356
He's waking.

36:31.525 --> 36:34.025
Park him at 45 degrees.

36:47.382 --> 36:50.368
Hey, boss, welcome back.

36:50.379 --> 36:52.057
Can you hear me?

36:53.189 --> 36:55.527
Now, you wanted to talk to me.

36:57.050 --> 36:59.934
Listen, man, whatever you know
that can help us,

36:59.945 --> 37:03.176
please, now is the time.

37:09.045 --> 37:10.545
He wants to write it down.

37:29.304 --> 37:31.087
"SEVER"?

37:32.336 --> 37:34.403
We got to figure out what this means.

37:38.614 --> 37:41.440
AUSTIN: You did good, man.
You're gonna be okay.

37:41.450 --> 37:42.682
(PHONE BUZZING)

37:47.460 --> 37:49.256
This is my dad.

37:56.945 --> 37:58.899
- Conrad.
- CONRAD: Dad.

37:58.910 --> 38:00.862
- You okay?
- Gordon Page

38:00.873 --> 38:02.717
would like to talk you.

38:02.728 --> 38:06.463
He wants proof that Abe
Benedict is alive.

38:08.768 --> 38:10.768
(PANTING)

38:12.104 --> 38:14.538
Okay. Put him on.

38:20.913 --> 38:22.905
Dr. Hawkins.

38:22.915 --> 38:24.273
(PANTING)

38:24.283 --> 38:25.741
SEVER.

38:25.751 --> 38:27.918
(PANTING)

38:31.017 --> 38:32.389
SEVER.

38:33.459 --> 38:35.265
You want proof, there it is.

38:35.276 --> 38:38.034
Abe Benedict is alive, and he's
talking about you and your company.

38:38.045 --> 38:40.349
There's nothing to talk about.
My company broke no rules.

38:40.360 --> 38:42.291
Made devices in China,

38:42.301 --> 38:44.277
copied faulty devices.

38:44.288 --> 38:46.812
- All the people you hurt.
- I hurt no one.

38:46.823 --> 38:50.389
Heart valves that failed. The VNS
device you put in an eight-year-old boy

38:50.400 --> 38:52.268
that stopped his heart over
and over again.

38:52.278 --> 38:53.900
I built this company from nothing.

38:53.911 --> 38:55.499
Abe was overcome with guilt.

38:55.510 --> 38:57.543
- Abe was a coward.
- No, he was a hero.

38:57.554 --> 38:59.741
Abe was gonna destroy everything
that I sacrificed for.

38:59.752 --> 39:02.825
- And you tried to kill him!
- I had no choice!

39:06.926 --> 39:08.410
Dad?

39:09.428 --> 39:11.295
Dad?

39:12.798 --> 39:14.798
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

39:17.203 --> 39:20.029
Earlier today, I...

39:20.039 --> 39:23.707
was admiring your $80,000 Rolex.

39:24.861 --> 39:27.536
It's not often that I change my watch

39:27.546 --> 39:30.037
in the middle of the day. Search him.

39:34.887 --> 39:36.654
Who's listening to us?

39:37.492 --> 39:40.651
- Who's listening to us?
- The FBI.

39:40.662 --> 39:42.829
Son of a bitch.

39:47.833 --> 39:48.990
Bring him.

39:49.001 --> 39:50.893
(GROANING)

39:50.903 --> 39:53.504
(PANTING)

39:55.328 --> 39:57.495
You're coming with me.

40:00.491 --> 40:02.825
We'll leave through the garage.

40:05.017 --> 40:07.310
FBI! Hands in the air! Freeze!

40:07.320 --> 40:09.845
(GUNSHOTS)

40:09.855 --> 40:11.388
They've got a hostage!

40:16.195 --> 40:19.522
